Bring a large #pot{} of water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

In a large #bowl{}, whisk together @sesame dressing{1.5%ounce}, @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%ounce}, @miso sauce concentrate{2}, @Dijon mustard{2%teaspoon}, @soy sauce{1.5%tbsp}, @rice wine vinegar{1/4%tsp}, and as many @Korean chili flakes{} as you like (we used half).

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @diced chicken thighs{10%ounce} in a single layer; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

> Rinse shrimp under cold water, then pat dry with paper towels, or open package of chicken and drain off any excess liquid.

Heat a large dry pan over medium-high heat. Add @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon} and toast, stirring frequently, until fragrant and golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Transfer to bowl with miso-sesame sauce.

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add @red cabbage and carrot mix{4%ounce} and @edamame{4%ounce}; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until just tender, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Meanwhile, trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}.

Once water is boiling, gently separate @Sun Noodle fresh noodles{10%ounce} and add to pot. Cook, stirring, until just tender, ~{2%minutes}.

Drain and rinse thoroughly under cold water, at least ~{30%seconds}. Shake off any excess water.

Transfer drained noodles to bowl with sauce. Using #tongs{}, toss until noodles are evenly coated.

Add half the scallions and half the stir-fried veggies; toss until evenly combined.

Divide noodles between bowls; top with remaining stir-fried veggies. Garnish with remaining scallions and serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.